{panel:bgColor=#eae6ff}
*Description*

For the funnel navigation improvements, when the user selects a plan, moves forward, then comes back to the plan selection page in the funnel, we want the plan they previously selected to be pre-selected.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*Resources*

* Design
* Assets
* Content, etc
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#ffebe6}
*Out of Scope* 

N/A
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria* *_(focus on the what, not the how)_*

* WHEN I am a logged out user OR I am a logged in user but I have no subscription yet (signed up, but haven‚Äôt checked out)
* AND I am on the checkout funnel past the plans selection page
* AND I go back to the plans selection page
* THEN I should see the plan I have previously selected pre-selected on the plans selection page
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#fffae6}
*Developer Information* 

* Does it require [release log|https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1Y9ZsoBL6vLG_HwEfAKSleYNHIslCTlEeAaJpU1c0evg/edit?gid=1092559263#gid=1092559263] record? (add ticket label: release-log)
* Do you recommend mobbing/pairing on this ticket?
* If applicable, caveats or other known dependencies
* Code context - examples of implementation
* ‚ö†Ô∏è If possible, avoid using redux and try to refactor the files you‚Äôre touching that depend on redux to use data access hooks. E.g to get subscription data you can use [this hook|https://github.com/hellofresh/web/blob/a5dcf829594c11a7355ad1df3844ca898be17aba/app/spaces/whitelabel/modules/whitelabel-web/packages/libraries/data-access/subscription/useCurrentSubscription.ts]  ‚ö†Ô∏è
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#deebff}
*User Story*

As a prospective Factorform customer who attempts to sign up or log in on the Legacy website ([http://factor75.com/factorform|http://factor75.com/factorform|smart-link] ), if I am not already registered, I must be smoothly and automatically redirected to the corresponding page on the new Shopify website ([https://factor-form-dev.myshopify.com/password|https://factor-form-dev.myshopify.com/password|smart-link]  ) to continue my session there. We have implemented these changes with a staging check as part of [https://hellofresh.atlassian.net/browse/MIO-20|https://hellofresh.atlassian.net/browse/MIO-20|smart-link], therefore this ticket is for removing the check and QA.
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e3fcef}
*Acceptance Criteria*

# Enable the redirection changes on live
# Verify the following user stories:
## If the user lands on the sign-up page, they are redirected to the Shopify sign-up page equivalent.
## If the user lands on the sign-in page, they are redirected to the Shopify sign-in page equivalent.
{panel}
